    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the differences in central venous catheter insertion
      time, success rate, and complication between thin-wall needle technique and
      catheter-over-the-needle technique for central venous catheterization in children.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Catheterization was performed using ultrasound with an &quot;out-of-plane&quot; approach by inserting
      the introducer needle (thin-wall needle technique) or Angiocath Plus™ catheter
      (catheter-over-the-needle technique) in 45 - 60° to the patient's skin while viewing the vein
      in a cross section.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
